  "text": "There were two studies specially comparing safety issues of extended infusion vs intermittent infusion of piperacillin/ tazobactam. Both intermittent and extended-infusion groups experienced similar incidence of acute renal injury in hospitalized patients, [CITATION_1] and comparable nephrotoxicity in patients with a creatinine clearance (CrCl)≥40 mL/min receiving at least 96-hour combination therapy of vancomycin and piperacillin/tazobactam. [CITATION_2] ",
